Metadata: Marina proposals for Commencement Bay: analysis of the permit review process
University of Washington Sea Grant, Seattle

This paper is an amount and analysis of the events involved in the application for permits needed to construct two contiguous marinas at the Outer Hylebos in CommenceMent Bay, Tacoma, Washington. The objective in doing so is, twofold: first, to understand the rationale behind major decisions made by the developers and reviewing governmental bodies; and secondly, to assess the quality and effectiveness of those decisions.
